      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "if there is a typo let's say i wanted to say \"assist\" but instead by I typed\n\"assit\" and it is not in the vocabulary, so it uses a  fallback mechanism called\nBPE(byte pair encoding) to split the unknown words into known words,\nwhich in this case it'll be \"ass\" and \"it\" because it is sandwitched between\ncan you it'll have two choices it's either help or assist, here comes the\nmathematical conclusion where it choses assist and fixes the typo",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 7,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "if there is a typo let's say i wanted to say \"assist\" but instead by I typed \"assit\" and it is not in the vocabulary, so it uses a  fallback mechanism called BPE(byte pair encoding) to split the unknown words into known words, which in this case it'll be \"ass\" and \"it\" because it is sandwitched between can you it'll have two choices it's either help or assist, here comes the mathematical conclusion where it choses assist and fixes the typo",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.15
    },
